---
import BaseLayout from "../layout/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "R10Progress: Advanced Golf Analytics for Garmin R10 Users";
const description =
  "Transform your Garmin R10 data into actionable golf insights with R10Progress. Free, open-source analytics tool for tracking progress, visualizing shot patterns, and improving your golf game.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="container">
    <section id="hero" aria-label="Introduction to R10Progress">
      <h1>R10Progress: Advanced Golf Analytics for Garmin R10 Users</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Looking for better insights from your Garmin R10 launch monitor? My
        free, open-source golf analytics platform transforms raw data into
        actionable improvements for your game.
      </p>
      <a
        class="button main"
        href="https://app.r10progress.com"
        aria-label="Start using R10Progress"
      >
        Start Analyzing Your Golf Data
      </a>
      <p
        class="open-source-note"
        style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-direction: column;"
      >
        <span class="highlight">✨ Free & Open Source Golf Analytics ✨</span>
        <span class="small-text"
          >(Premium AI swing analysis available through optional donations)</span
        >
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="about" aria-label="About R10Progress">
      <h2>Why Garmin R10 Users Need Better Golf Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        As a fellow Garmin R10 user, I found the standard app's analytics too
        limited for serious improvement. That's why I created R10Progress - a
        comprehensive golf data analysis tool designed specifically for Garmin
        R10 users who want to take their game to the next level.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unlike corporate golf software, R10Progress is a passion project built
        by me, a golfer, for other golfers. The open-source approach means the
        entire golf community can contribute to making it even better!
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="features" aria-label="R10Progress Features">
      <h2>Essential Golf Analytics Features for Garmin R10 Users</h2>
      <p>
        I've designed R10Progress to transform your Garmin R10 data into
        meaningful insights with powerful visualization tools, progress
        tracking, and detailed analytics - all presented in golfer-friendly
        language without the technical jargon.
      </p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Visual Shot Analysis</strong> - Transform raw Garmin R10 data into
          intuitive visual representations
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Golf Performance Tracking</strong> - Monitor your improvement with
          detailed metrics over time
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Club Comparison Analytics</strong> - Identify your strongest and
          weakest clubs with data-driven insights
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Personalized Golf Goals</strong> - Set and track achievable targets
          based on your actual performance
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Swing Pattern Recognition</strong> - Identify the root causes of
          common swing issues like slices and hooks
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="images-container">
        <div>
          <h3>Golf Session Dashboard</h3>
          <p>
            Compare your latest range session against your historical
            performance with my intuitive dashboard. Spot trends and
            improvements without needing to be a statistics expert.
          </p>
          <img
            alt="R10Progress golf session dashboard showing comprehensive Garmin R10 statistics"
            src="/assets/averagespersession.png"
            loading="lazy"
            width="600"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Golf Shot Dispersion Analysis</h3>
          <p>
            Visualize exactly where your shots land with detailed dispersion
            patterns for each club. Gain insights into your consistency and
            accuracy that the standard Garmin app doesn't provide.
          </p>
          <img
            alt="R10Progress golf shot dispersion analysis showing accurate landing patterns from Garmin R10 data"
            src="/assets/shotdispersion.png"
            loading="lazy"
            width="600"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Golf Swing Correlation Analysis</h3>
          <p>
            Discover the relationships between different aspects of your golf
            swing. Learn whether increasing club head speed actually improves
            your distance, and other crucial insights for game improvement.
          </p>
          <img
            alt="R10Progress golf swing correlation charts analyzing relationships between different swing metrics"
            src="/assets/shotscatterplot.png"
            loading="lazy"
            width="600"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Comprehensive Golf Data Organization</h3>
          <p>
            Access all your Garmin R10 shot data in one centralized location,
            with powerful sorting and filtering options. Perfect for detailed
            analysis or sharing progress with your golf instructor.
          </p>
          <img
            alt="R10Progress organized golf data tables showing comprehensive Garmin R10 statistics"
            src="/assets/averagestable.png"
            loading="lazy"
            width="600"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Golf Improvement Goal Tracking</h3>
          <p>
            Set realistic, data-driven golf improvement goals based on your
            actual performance metrics. Track your progress over time and
            celebrate meaningful achievements in your golf journey.
          </p>
          <img
            alt="R10Progress golf improvement goal tracking showing progress metrics for Garmin R10 users"
            src="/assets/goals.png"
            loading="lazy"
            width="600"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="language-support" aria-label="Language Support">
      <h2>Multi-Language Support for Garmin R10 Users Worldwide</h2>
      <p>
        R10Progress currently supports Garmin Golf .csv files exported in
        English, Spanish, and German. This means you can analyze your golf data
        regardless of your device's language settings.
      </p>
      <p class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Need Support for Another Language?</strong> I'm happy to add support
        for additional languages! Simply send me an example .csv file from your Garmin
        Golf app, and I'll expand the compatibility to include your language.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="ai-feature" aria-label="AI Golf Analysis">
      <h2>AI-Powered Golf Swing Analysis for Garmin R10 Users</h2>
      <p>
        Take your golf game even further with my AI-powered swing analysis that
        provides personalized tips based on your unique Garmin R10 data
        patterns. This advanced feature delivers insights similar to what you'd
        get from a professional golf coach.
      </p>
      <p>
        The AI analysis feature is available for a small donation (about $5, the
        price of a coffee) to help cover the API costs while keeping the core
        R10Progress platform completely free for all golfers.
      </p>
      <p class="highlight-box">
        <strong>100% Optional Enhancement:</strong> All core R10Progress golf analytics
        features remain completely free forever. The AI analysis is simply an additional
        tool for those wanting even deeper insights.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="releases" aria-label="R10Progress Updates">
      <h2>Continuous Improvement for Garmin R10 Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        I'm constantly evolving R10Progress with new features and improvements
        based on feedback from the community of Garmin R10 users. The
        open-source approach means anyone can contribute ideas or code!
      </p>
      <p>
        View the latest updates or suggest new features on the <a
          href="/release">release page</a
        >. For developers and technically-minded golfers, visit the <a
          href="https://github.com/r10progress/r10progress">GitHub repository</a
        > to explore the code or contribute to the project.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="cta" aria-label="Call to Action">
      <h2>Start Improving Your Golf Game with R10Progress Today</h2>
      <p>
        Join hundreds of Garmin R10 users who are transforming their golf game
        with this free, comprehensive analytics platform. No subscriptions, no
        hidden fees.
      </p>
      <a
        class="button main"
        href="https://app.r10progress.com"
        aria-label="Begin using R10Progress"
      >
        Analyze Your Garmin R10 Data Now
      </a>
      <p class="open-source-note">
        Developed with ❤️ by a passionate golfer just like you
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    & > *:nth-child(even) {
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .feature-list {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .testimonial-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .testimonial {
    background: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .testimonial-author {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  #cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1rem;
  }

  .open-source-note {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .highlight {
    background-color: #fffacd;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .testimonial-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .small-text {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .highlight-box {
    background-color: #f0f8ff;
    border-left: 4px solid #0066cc;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
</style>
